and then getting you right into
the news, they're setting you

471
00:20:49,286 --> 00:20:51,166 A:middle
up for success in a
different kind of way.

472
00:20:52,056 --> 00:20:54,516 A:middle
And this approach
is not appropriate

473
00:20:54,516 --> 00:20:56,176 A:middle
for all kinds of apps or games.

474
00:20:56,776 --> 00:20:59,136 A:middle
It's really when you're
breaking into a new market

475
00:20:59,256 --> 00:21:01,636 A:middle
or that you're establishing
some sort of new paradigm

476

477
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00,000

478
00:20:59,256 --> 00:21:01,636 A:middle
or that you're establishing
some sort of new paradigm

479
00:21:02,116 --> 00:21:04,396 A:middle
that you might need to
communicate just a little bit

480
00:21:04,856 --> 00:21:05,936 A:middle
about your core concept.

481
00:21:05,936 --> 00:21:09,276 A:middle
And that's going to help
people understand the products

482
00:21:09,276 --> 00:21:11,076 A:middle
and quite frankly,
appreciate it, right?

483
00:21:11,906 --> 00:21:15,256 A:middle
So, just three short screens and
then getting you into the news

484
00:21:15,256 --> 00:21:16,946 A:middle
because they're going to
get out of the way quickly.

485
00:21:17,496 --> 00:21:21,726 A:middle
So think about the basic, basic
things that people would need

486
00:21:21,726 --> 00:21:24,076 A:middle
to know in order to
start playing your game

487
00:21:24,076 --> 00:21:25,786 A:middle
or using your app.

488
00:21:25,856 --> 00:21:28,676 A:middle
And think about if any of
them really need explaining,

489
00:21:29,216 --> 00:21:32,176 A:middle
because again, if you
don't - if they don't,

490
00:21:32,176 --> 00:21:33,596 A:middle
don't do any onboarding, right?

491
00:21:33,956 --> 00:21:38,006 A:middle
But if you do, consider
the ways that you can start

492
00:21:38,006 --> 00:21:40,596 A:middle
with the basics and
build up the complexity.

493
00:21:41,066 --> 00:21:44,296 A:middle
With games, it's going to be how
to move, what's the objective,

494
00:21:44,676 --> 00:21:46,426 A:middle
how do you win and
things like that.

495
00:21:47,626 --> 00:21:49,186 A:middle
And when you're teaching
these things,

496
00:21:50,036 --> 00:21:52,716 A:middle
make sure you're only
teaching one thing at a time.

497
00:21:53,766 --> 00:21:57,126 A:middle
It is so much harder to learn
if you're dealt with a bunch

498
00:21:57,126 --> 00:21:59,326 A:middle
of instructions at
once or if it's -

499
00:21:59,326 --> 00:22:01,606 A:middle
especially if it's related to
something unfamiliar, right?

