00:25:04,816 --> 00:25:07,416 A:middle
So "Leo's Fortune" -
one skill at a time,

578
00:25:07,556 --> 00:25:10,776 A:middle
which is so manageable, and
it's fun because you're playing.

579
00:25:11,816 --> 00:25:14,006 A:middle
So it's a great example
of scaffolding,

580
00:25:14,766 --> 00:25:18,236 A:middle
along with "Hitman GO" and
several other examples.

581
00:25:19,826 --> 00:25:22,866 A:middle
So the first thing you do,
is you learn the objective,

582
00:25:23,786 --> 00:25:25,136 A:middle
collect those gold coins.

583
00:25:26,536 --> 00:25:27,576 A:middle
Next thing you're going to learn

584
00:25:27,576 --> 00:25:30,136 A:middle
about is the optimal
hand position, right?

585
00:25:30,206 --> 00:25:32,706 A:middle
So they're building up the
complexity with the scaffolding.

586
00:25:33,286 --> 00:25:35,686 A:middle
And the next thing
that you learn

587
00:25:35,686 --> 00:25:38,936 A:middle
about is really basic
movement - how to go forwards,

588
00:25:39,086 --> 00:25:42,546 A:middle
what are you doing
with your left hand?

589
00:25:42,716 --> 00:25:44,116 A:middle
Next step is obstacles,

590
00:25:44,606 --> 00:25:47,856 A:middle
which you conquer using your
